summary:
The Security Council, 
Taking note of letters from the Secretary-General and the President of the International Criminal Tribunal for Rwanda, 
Recalling resolutions 955 (1994) and 1901 (2009), 
Recalling the Completion Strategy, which called for the Tribunal to complete its work in 2010, 
Noting the Tribunal's assessment that it will not complete all its work in 2010, 
Decides to: 
1. Authorize Judges Joseph Asoka de Silva, Taghrid Hikmet, and Joseph Masanche to complete specific cases beyond their term expiry; 
2. Allow the temporary increase of ad litem judges from nine to twelve to facilitate trial completion; 
3. Urge staff retention and Tribunal focus on core functions; 
4. Remain seized of the matter.
